0.5
0.5
```

Rather than checking twice for `line[0] != '#'`, I think this could be simplified to:

```python
if line[0] == '#':
    continue

parse_line = line.strip().split('=')
if len(parse_line) == 2:
    # ...
else:
    # ...
```

