@galgalesh Nice, thanks!

Would there ever be a case where you had more than one database and you had to know which one is which? And if that's the case, how can you differentiate between those databases using the relation interface? For example, if you had created one table in postgres A and different table in postgres B and wanted to update the table in postgres B.

I guess what I'm trying to find out is if there is going to be problematic with the current relation interface model for charms that need to manage multiple applications using the same relation since they are just a collection and not separate objects.

